<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1029,2028]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1281,1307]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dall, W. H." box="[323,454,1281,1307]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" pagination="1 - 134" refId="ref33356" refString="Dall, W. H. (1927) Small shells from dredgings off the southeast coast of the United States by the United States Fisheries Steam- er &quot; Albatross &quot; in 1885 and 1886. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 70 (2667), 1 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.70 - 2667.1" type="journal article" year="1927">Dall (1927)</bibRefCitation>
recorded four specimens in the original description. 
<bibRefCitation author="Waren, A. &amp; Sibuet, M." box="[1056,1320,1281,1307]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" pagination="103 - 107" refId="ref38009" refString="Waren, A. &amp; Sibuet, M. (1981) Ophieulima (Mollusca, Prosobranchia), a new genus of ophiuroid parasites. Sarsia, 66, 103 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00364827.1981.10414528" type="journal article" year="1981">Warén &amp; Sibuet (1981)</bibRefCitation>
described two 
<typeStatus box="[201,308,1317,1343]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">paratypes</typeStatus>
under the same catalog number as the 
<typeStatus box="[752,854,1317,1343]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">holotype</typeStatus>
. No other specimen than the 
<typeStatus box="[1185,1283,1317,1343]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-52@35.[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. A–G. Ophieulima minima (Dall, 1927). A, G. Holotype of Stilifer minima Dall, 1927, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Figure 19A, G</figureCitation>
) was found in the USNM and the status of these other shells is unknown or they are presumed lost (E. Strong, personal communication). 
<bibRefCitation author="Waren, A. &amp; Sibuet, M." box="[414,731,1389,1415]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" pagination="103 - 107" refId="ref38009" refString="Waren, A. &amp; Sibuet, M. (1981) Ophieulima (Mollusca, Prosobranchia), a new genus of ophiuroid parasites. Sarsia, 66, 103 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00364827.1981.10414528" type="journal article" year="1981">Warén &amp; Sibuet (1981: 384)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed the species and noted that the variation in shape of the type specimens is great and that the identification of the material by them is questionable, because the northeast Atlantic specimens studied are even broader than the types. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." box="[819,1157,1461,1487]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén (1986: 348)</bibRefCitation>
also considered the shell morphology of the species quite variable, with an evident sexual dimorphism (males are half the size of females).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1029,2028]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">
Beside the variation in size and shape correlated with the sexual dimorphism, a variation in shell sculpture can also be observed. 
<bibRefCitation author="Waren, A. &amp; Sibuet, M." box="[352,671,1569,1595]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" pagination="103 - 107" refId="ref38009" refString="Waren, A. &amp; Sibuet, M. (1981) Ophieulima (Mollusca, Prosobranchia), a new genus of ophiuroid parasites. Sarsia, 66, 103 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00364827.1981.10414528" type="journal article" year="1981">Warén &amp; Sibuet (1981: 384)</bibRefCitation>
commented that none of the types shows the spiral striation that occurs in some well-preserved specimens from the Northeast Atlantic examined by them. The latter authors described this spiral sculpture as irregular, extremely fine scratch-like striae present in some small areas of the shell that are less corroded in such specimens. The examination of SEM images of the 
<typeStatus box="[978,1076,1677,1703]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Waren &amp; Sibuet" authorityYear="1981" box="[1115,1338,1677,1703]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Ophieulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[1115,1338,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Ophieulima minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(USNM 108039) (
<figureCitation box="[261,429,1713,1739]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-52@35.[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. A–G. Ophieulima minima (Dall, 1927). A, G. Holotype of Stilifer minima Dall, 1927, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Figure 19A, G</figureCitation>
) has not revealed the presence of the spiral scratch-like striae, but only the axial growth lines. 
<bibRefCitation author="Romani, L. &amp; Bartolini, S. &amp; Giusti, F. &amp; Sbrana, C." box="[219,454,1749,1775]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" pagination="131" refId="ref36289" refString="Romani, L., Bartolini, S., Giusti, F. &amp; Sbrana, C. (2014) Ophieulima (Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda: Eulimidae): a new genus for the Mediterranean Sea. Marine Biodiversity Records, 7, E 131. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 1755267214001304" type="journal article" year="2014">
Romani 
<emphasis box="[315,372,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Waren &amp; Sibuet" authorityYear="1981" box="[562,681,1749,1775]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Ophieulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[562,681,1749,1775]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">O. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Mediterranean and did not observe the spiral sculpture in very fresh shells, with dried specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1029,2028]" lastBlockId="35.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="486" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">
The single shell from 
<collectingCountry box="[449,517,1821,1847]" name="Brazil" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Brazil</collectingCountry>
agrees well with the 
<typeStatus box="[760,867,1821,1847]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">paratypes</typeStatus>
illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." box="[1031,1312,1821,1847]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén (1986</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 827– 830) in the general shape (
<figureCitation box="[447,611,1857,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-52@35.[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. A–G. Ophieulima minima (Dall, 1927). A, G. Holotype of Stilifer minima Dall, 1927, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Figure 19B, C</figureCitation>
), number of whorls of the larval shell (=3.0 whorls) (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1339,1857,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-52@35.[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. A–G. Ophieulima minima (Dall, 1927). A, G. Holotype of Stilifer minima Dall, 1927, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Figure 19G</figureCitation>
) and the axial sculpture of faint growth lines (
<figureCitation box="[574,744,1893,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-52@35.[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. A–G. Ophieulima minima (Dall, 1927). A, G. Holotype of Stilifer minima Dall, 1927, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Figure 19C, D</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[817,915,1893,1919]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Waren &amp; Sibuet" authorityYear="1981" box="[955,1180,1893,1919]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Ophieulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[955,1180,1893,1919]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Ophieulima minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents a protoconch with about 2.6 whorls and 
<quantity box="[454,542,1929,1956]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" unit="mm" value="195.0">195 µm</quantity>
in diameter (
<figureCitation box="[693,825,1929,1955]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-52@35.[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. A–G. Ophieulima minima (Dall, 1927). A, G. Holotype of Stilifer minima Dall, 1927, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Figure 19G</figureCitation>
) and the shell from 
<collectingCountry box="[1055,1123,1929,1955]" name="Brazil" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Brazil</collectingCountry>
has 3.0 protoconch whorls, 
<quantity box="[151,238,1965,1991]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" unit="mm" value="210.0">210 µm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[313,442,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-52@35.[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. A–G. Ophieulima minima (Dall, 1927). A, G. Holotype of Stilifer minima Dall, 1927, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Figure 19F</figureCitation>
). The teleoconch of the 
<typeStatus box="[709,807,1965,1991]" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Waren &amp; Sibuet" authorityYear="1981" box="[844,962,1965,1991]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Ophieulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[844,962,1965,1991]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">O. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the shell from 
<collectingCountry box="[1177,1245,1965,1991]" name="Brazil" pageId="34" pageNumber="485">Brazil</collectingCountry>
have about three whorls, but the former reaches 
<quantity box="[499,585,2001,2027]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
long and the latter reaches 
<quantity box="[892,978,2001,2027]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="34" pageNumber="485" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
long, which represents about 65% of the shell length of the 
<typeStatus box="[357,459,151,177]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">holotype</typeStatus>
. The shell from 
<collectingCountry box="[638,706,151,177]" name="Brazil" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Brazil</collectingCountry>
is fairly corroded, as can be seen from the several pits in the shell surface (
<figureCitation box="[247,373,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetId="figure-52@35.[151,1435,237,1900]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 19. A–G. Ophieulima minima (Dall, 1927). A, G. Holotype of Stilifer minima Dall, 1927, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Figure 19F</figureCitation>
) and spiral sculpture was not observed.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4542977" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4542977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4542977/files/figure.png" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" startId="35.[151,250,1924,1948]" targetBox="[151,1435,237,1900]" targetPageId="35">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,1924,2020]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,1924,1948]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">FIGURE 19.</emphasis>
A–G. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dall, 1927)" baseAuthorityName="Dall" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[351,684,1924,1948]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Ophieulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[351,552,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Ophieulima minima</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dall, W. H." box="[565,676,1924,1948]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" pagination="1 - 134" refId="ref33356" refString="Dall, W. H. (1927) Small shells from dredgings off the southeast coast of the United States by the United States Fisheries Steam- er &quot; Albatross &quot; in 1885 and 1886. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 70 (2667), 1 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.70 - 2667.1" type="journal article" year="1927">Dall, 1927</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. A, G. Holotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dall, 1927" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1927" box="[876,1140,1924,1948]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Stilifer" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[876,1027,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="486">Stilifer minima</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dall, W. H." box="[1032,1140,1924,1948]" pageId="35" pageNumber="486" pagination="1 - 134" refId="ref33356" refString="Dall, W. H. (1927) Small shells from dredgings off the southeast coast of the United States by the United States Fisheries Steam- er &quot; Albatross &quot; in 1885 and 1886. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 70 (2667), 1 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.70 - 2667.1" type="journal article" year="1927">Dall, 1927</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, USNM 108039. B–F. MNRJ 35223. E. Detail of protoconch, frontal view. F, G. Detail of protoconch, apical view. Scale bars: A–D= 1.0 mm; E= 100 µm; F= 75 µm; G= 50 µm. Credits: A, G, courtesy of USNM.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">
Even with these small differences in size, shape, and sculpture, the shell from 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1130,151,177]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Brazil</collectingCountry>
is identified as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dall" baseAuthorityYear="1927" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Ophieulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Ophieulima minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This represents the southernmost record of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dall" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[743,863,187,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Ophieulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minima">
<emphasis box="[743,863,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">O. minima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is possible that further material and other techniques will uncover more species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Waren &amp; Sibuet" authorityYear="1981" box="[562,694,223,249]" class="Gastropoda" family="Eulimidae" genus="Ophieulima" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[562,694,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Ophieulima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than currently expected in the whole Atlantic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,519,258,284]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Geographical distribution.</emphasis>
Northeastern Atlantic: South 
<collectingCountry box="[860,942,259,285]" name="Iceland" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Iceland</collectingCountry>
to South of the Bay of Biscay (
<bibRefCitation author="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A." pageId="36" pageNumber="487" pagination="299 - 576" refId="ref32770" refString="Bouchet, P. &amp; Waren, A. (1986) Revision of the northeast Atlantic bathyal and abyssal Aclididae, Eulimidae, Epitoniidae (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Bollettino Malacologico, Supplemento 2, 299 - 576. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 140762" type="journal article" year="1986">Bouchet &amp; Warén 1986</bibRefCitation>
); Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Romani, L. &amp; Bartolini, S. &amp; Giusti, F. &amp; Sbrana, C." box="[492,717,295,321]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" pagination="131" refId="ref36289" refString="Romani, L., Bartolini, S., Giusti, F. &amp; Sbrana, C. (2014) Ophieulima (Gastropoda: Caenogastropoda: Eulimidae): a new genus for the Mediterranean Sea. Marine Biodiversity Records, 7, E 131. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 1755267214001304" type="journal article" year="2014">
Romani 
<emphasis box="[591,648,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
); Azorean seamounts (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoffman, L. &amp; Freiwald, A." box="[973,1282,295,321]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" pagination="81 - 99" refId="ref34137" refString="Hoffman, L. &amp; Freiwald, A. (2020) Bathyal Eulimidae (Gastropoda: Vanikoridoidea) from the Azorean seamounts collected during the R / V Meteor Cruise M 151 Athena. Miscellanea Malacologica, 8 (6), 81 - 99." type="journal article" year="2020">Hoffman &amp; Freiwald 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Western Atlantic: 
<collectingCountry box="[228,288,331,357]" name="United States of America" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">USA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingCountry box="[299,389,331,357]" name="Georgia" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Georgia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dall, W. H." box="[403,520,331,357]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" pagination="1 - 134" refId="ref33356" refString="Dall, W. H. (1927) Small shells from dredgings off the southeast coast of the United States by the United States Fisheries Steam- er &quot; Albatross &quot; in 1885 and 1886. Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 70 (2667), 1 - 134. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.70 - 2667.1" type="journal article" year="1927">Dall 1927</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingCountry box="[540,613,331,357]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[622,714,331,357]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
(present study).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,151,393]" box="[199,777,366,393]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,504,366,392]" pageId="36" pageNumber="487">Bathymetric distribution.</emphasis>
From 
<quantity box="[579,650,366,393]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.52" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" unit="m" value="452.0">452 m</quantity>
to 
<quantity box="[685,773,367,393]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="36" pageNumber="487" unit="m" value="2100.0">2100 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
